<br>
(no kicks to bards, I like a well played bard in my groups, but they ain't the masters or even close of melee. Songs = good. Melee = crap for bards.)<br>
<br>
I'd like our pets to tank a lil more than they do, and be able to tank worth a damn, just so we can take a break and heal ourselves. We are the only class that can heal ourselves and have a decent pet (I'm not including charmed druid crap, BTW) and we also melee and take aggro sometimes, unlike a mage or a necromancer (normally. Aggro for necro = FD ... mage = scream for a peel). So, sometimes I like taking time out while my pet tanks so I can run back in like a tag team wrestler.<br>
<br>
Unlike mages, necromancers or any other pet class, our pets are often our equals and partners. A mage or necromancer doesn't have any raw melee output like their pets. Spells, yes, not melee. We do. We are there in the thick of things with our pets, not just standing off to the sidelines. It's a very different relationship, and it needs to be treated uniquely. We are not just mages or necromancers who melee. We are not just shamans with a bigger pet.<br>
<br>
Raimundo Rex, 24th Gatorboy of Rodcet Nife. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/beqbeastlord.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=zyrexxshadowfyre>Zyrexx Shadowfyre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF9933>(9/27/02 6:28:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3675.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Beastlord melee</span><hr size=1> ****summoned staves = melee/dps****<br>
